Quick start:

1. Include airbag_fd.cpp and airbag_fd.h in your project.
2. Define the appropriate HAVE_* symbols somehow.
3. Call one of the airbag_init_* functions early.
4. Post-crash (perhaps in a watchdog or on next startup) harvest crash logs.

Example test:

$ g++ -O -W -Wall -DHAVE_STRSIGNAL -DHAVE_EXECINFO_H -DHAVE_DLADDR airbag_fd.cpp airbag_fd_test.cpp -o airbag_fd_test -ldl
$ ./airbag_fd_test.sh

